snippet.textDisplay:
Currently in Shelter in Place, in the worst county in the state of Michigan. We also share a main street with Detroit City which has so many cases, they have their own daily case and death counter. :( Our community is uplifting and supporting all our local ER, hospitals, etc.


An exhibit hall in downtown Detroit will start accepting 1000 patients tomorrow, Tuesday April 7. The drs, nurses, tradesmen and construction crews all have to stay downtown at the site.



We are staying home, figuring out how to have groceries delivered. We started growing basil and green onions and will likely start to save any cuttings that re-grow.



Local currency is toilet paper, flour, sugar, milk, eggs and in our family's case, strawberry yogurt.


We celebrated one birthday from car to balcony, leaving gifts and baked goods on the porch. We then taught the parents how to use Zoom for family get - together calls.


:) Detroit makes it happen.
